The White House Office of the Press Secretary held a press briefing on March 7, 2013. During the briefing, Press Secretary Jay Carney discussed a range of topics, including gun violence legislation, North Korea’s threat of a nuclear strike on the United States, the President’s outreach to Republicans, and the use of drones in the United States. Carney also mentioned that the President was pleased with the dinner he had with Republicans the night before and that he would continue to engage with lawmakers from both parties on a range of issues.